'''Moses Israel Fürst''' (died circa 1692) was a [[merchant]] and [[financier]] of [[Hamburg]], [[Germany]]. He was also active as a [[Court Jew]], a term describing the role of historical [[Jewish]] bankers or businessmen who lent money and managed finances of some of the [[Europe]]an [[Nobility|noble]] houses. From 1688 onwards, Fürst held the tobacco monopoly in the state of [[Mecklenburg]]-[[Schwerin]]  together with fellow merchant [[Michael Hinrichsen]].

