'''PROTERRA''', or Programme for Land Redistribution and Stimulation of Agroindustry in the North and Northeast, was a Brazilian government programme of the 1970s to address rural poverty founded following the approval of the Land Statute in 1964.<ref>Gary N. Howe, David Goodman ''Smallholders and Structural Change in the Brazilian Economy''</ref> In the [[Amazon basin]] it was supported by the [[World Bank]].<ref>Anthony L. Hall ''Developing Amazonia'' 1989 </ref>
